{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "SOP/break", "tags": "model"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Break"], "extent": [31, 41]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Breaks the input geometry using the specified cutting shape."], "extent": [41, 110]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [110, 125], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool cuts a model along a jagged cutting plane. The cutting plane can also be switched to a box, sphere, or custom object. You can then use the pieces with the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdfracturedobject", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Fractured Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdfracturedobject.html"}, " or ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Glue Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject.html"}, ". This will automatically clean up the faces, and unique the points so you don\u2019t see the cracks."], "extent": [125, 483]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdfracturedobject", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Fractured Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdfracturedobject.html"}, " and ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Glue Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject.html"}, " automatically add an ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/assemble", "type": "link", "text": ["Assemble"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/assemble.html"}, " node after any breaks, which creates groups for each piece of broken geometry."], "extent": [483, 709]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The Break tool creates a single jagged cut with manual control, whereas ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/shatter", "type": "link", "text": ["Shatter"], "fullpath": "/shelf/shatter.html"}, " creates multiple random cuts automatically."], "extent": [709, 851]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [851, 857], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This tool only works on polygons."], "extent": [857, 896]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "includeme", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using Break"], "extent": [896, 926], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "indent": 0, "text": ["Select the object you want to break."], "extent": [926, 967]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "indent": 0, "text": ["Click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SOP/break", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/break.html"}, {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/break", "type": "link", "text": ["Break"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/break.html"}, " tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Model"]}, " tab."], "extent": [967, 1046], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You can do this multiple times to create multiple breaks in a single geometry object."], "extent": [1046, 1141]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/shelf/break.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [1141, 1178]}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1178, 1184], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["By default, the Break tool will select connected primitives. If you want to select individual faces, right-click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "TOOLS/select_faces", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/TOOLS/select_faces.html"}, " component mode button on the left toolbar and turn off ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Select Connected Geometry"]}, "."], "extent": [1184, 1418]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["You can then turn your object into an ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdfracturedobject", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Fracture Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdfracturedobject.html"}, " or an ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject", "type": "link", "text": ["RBD Glue Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject.html"}, ".    "], "extent": [1418, 1559]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1559, 1564], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If you want to simulate pieces breaking off of something else, for example rocks breaking off a cliff, you can use the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/extract", "type": "link", "text": ["extract"], "fullpath": "/shelf/extract.html"}, " tool to separate the static objects from dynamic objects."], "extent": [1564, 1771]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If you do not want to use this tool with dynamics, you will need to append an ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/assemble", "type": "link", "text": ["Assemble SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/assemble.html"}, ". Turning the object into an RBD Fracture Object or an RBD Glue Object will create the Assemble node for you."], "extent": [1771, 1991]}]}], "title": ["Break"], "summary": ["Breaks the input geometry using the specified cutting shape."]}